); clypeus distinctly concave and thick medio-ventrally (

). eye in dorsal view 1.1 × as wide as temple; interocular distance at middle of face 4.3 × distance between antennal toruli.

Mesosoma.
Mesosoma 1.4 × as long as high (

); mesopleuron largely punctate-rugose, becoming densely punctate posteriorly; transverse mesopleural groove narrow, crenulate (

); notauli wide, deep and coarsely crenulate (

); middle lobe of mesoscutum transversely punctate-rugose, lateral lobes densely punctate anteriorly, becoming punctate-rugose posteriorly (

); scutellar sulcus complete, moderately narrow and crenulate; scutellum coarsely rugose, convex laterally and shallowly concave medially, anteriorly distinctly above level of mesoscutum; metanotum slightly convex, highly setose (

); propodeum largely punctate-rugose, becoming smooth posteriorly (

); posterior propodeal carina distinctly arched, narrow lamelliform, foramen comparatively narrow and as high as wide basally.

Wings
. Fore wing with length of vein 1-M 1.3 × as long as vein 1-SR, vein 1-M curved and vein 1-SR straight; subdiscal and discal cells less setose (

); second submarginal cell sessile anteriorly, 1.4 × as long as third cell, connecting with discal cell by forming a vertical vein.

Metasoma.
First metasomal tergite 1.1 × as wide as long, smooth and with shallow but wide depression medially (

); second tergite narrowly smooth and shiny medially, moderately punctate laterally; following tergites moderately punctate (

), black spot in the middle of yellow posterior band of second tergite narrow; second sternite slightly convex, densely punctate (

); third sternite without depression, densely punctate; following sternites densely punctate; visible part of third sternite 0.2 × as long as second sternite.
